    "It is worth noting that sometimes n of the Beltrami differentials are taken to act on these states to give terms of the form JHEP04(2024)048Σg Ĝ- -1 Ψ i.The ghost fields ρ, σ, H 1 and H 2 all form ϵ = -1 linear dilaton type theories in the hybrid formalism (see appendix C) and carry background chargesq ρ = 3, q σ = 3i, q H 1 = q H 2 = i,as can be read off from the stress tensors in (2.10) and (2.11).",
    "This implies that the overall ghost contribution for a non-vanishing correlator must be [7] e (g-1)(-3ρ-3iσ-iH), to act as an appropriate screening operator.",
    "Let's consider a general term in (B.1) with k insertions of G -and n + 3g -3 -k insertions of G-.",
    "Then the overall ghost contribution is given by k × (ghosts of G -) + (n + 3g -3 -k) × (ghosts of G-) + (g -1) × (ghosts of G+)+ n × (ghosts of physical state insertions).According to (2.10) and (2.11), the possible ghost contributions of G -are either -iσ, -iH 1 or -iH 2, whilst those of Gare (-2ρ -iσ -iH), (-ρ -iH), (-ρ -iσ -iH 1) or (-ρ -iσ -iH 2) and for G+ they are (ρ + iH), (ρ + iσ + iH 1) or (ρ + iσ + iH 2).",
